{{Youmay|the apartment that [[Han Solo/Legends|Han]] and [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] lived in with their children during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]]|the [[Solos' apartment|apartment]] they lived in shortly after getting [[Wedding of Han Solo and Leia Organa/Legends|married]]}}
The '''Solo apartment''' referred to the [[Solo family/Legends|Solo family's]] home on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] after they moved out of the [[Imperial Palace/Legends|Imperial Palace]], located in [[Eastport/Legends|Eastport's]] administrative district. It was situated some three hundred meters from the top of its building, making it nearly a penthouse suite by the standards of that [[Planet/Legends|world]].

The apartment was abandoned when [[Han Solo/Legends|Han]] and [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia]] were forced to evacuate the capital in the face of the [[Yuuzhan Vong]]'s [[Battle of Coruscant (Yuuzhan Vong War)|conquest of Coruscant]]. Some time later [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]], who was wandering the [[Terraforming/Legends|Vongformed]] planet after having escaped from Vong captivity with the help of [[Vergere]], stumbled upon the remains of the apartment. Dejected and wondering what was going on, he eventually began conversing with the [[Force ghost/Legends|Force ghost]] of his dead sibling, [[Anakin Solo|Anakin]]; shortly thereafter several Yuuzhan Vong warriors, led by [[Nom Anor]], recaptured Jacen there.

